to the C function `archive_read_disk_set_behavior`;\n        use the `libarchive.flags.READDISK_*` constants\n    lookup (bool):\n        when True, the C function `archive_read_disk_set_standard_lookup`\n        is called to enable the lookup of user and group names\n    pathname (str | None):\n        the path of the file in the archive, defaults to the source path\n    recursive (bool):\n        when False, if a path in `paths` is a directory,\n        only the directory itself is added.\n    attributes (dict): passed to `ArchiveEntry.modify()`\n\nRaises:\n    ArchiveError: if a file doesn't exist or can't be accessed, or if\n                  adding it to the archive fails"]}, {"name": "libarchive.write.ArchiveWrite.add_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kw", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "libarchive.write.ArchiveWrite.add_file_from_memory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "entry_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "entry_size", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "entry_data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filetype", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "permission", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**other_attributes", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["\"Add file from memory to archive.\n\nArgs:\n    entry_path (str | bytes): the file's path\n    entry_size (int): the file's size, in bytes\n    entry_data (bytes | Iterable[bytes]): the file's content\n    filetype (int): see `libarchive.entry.ArchiveEntry.modify()`\n    permission (int): see `libarchive.entry.ArchiveEntry.modify()`\n    other_attributes: see `libarchive.entry.ArchiveEntry.modify()`"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []},